headline: Dining Stocks Have Been Failing. How These Survivors Are Racking Up the Returns.
summary: Bankruptcies have left the casual dining scene to a group of best-of-breed companies, from Brinker International’s Chili’s to Texas Roadhouse, Darden Restaurants, and maybe even Starbucks. A warning: anti-obesity drugs aren’t going away.
